description: A neuroacanthocytosis that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VPS13A gene, which encodes chorein, on chromosome 9q21; it is characterized by progressive neurodegeneration and red cell acanthocytosis, with onset in the third to fifth decade of life.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency, nuclear type 1
description: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has material basis in mutation in the ATPAF2 gene on chromosome 17p11.

name: non-syndromic X-linked intellectual disability
description: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by a X-linked inheritance pattern.

name: Joubert syndrome
description: A ciliopathy that is characterized by congenital malformation of the brainstem and agenesis or hypoplasia of the cerebellar vermis leading to an abnormal respiratory pattern, nystagmus, hypotonia, ataxia, and delay in achieving motor milestones.

name: Meckel syndrome
description: A ciliopathy that is characterized by renal cystic dysplasia, occipital encephalocele, polydactyly (post axial), hepatic developmental defects, and pulmonary hypoplasia.

name: hydrolethalus syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by mulitple fetal developmental defects including polydactyly and central nervous system malformations that results from a single amino acid mutation of D211G of the HYLS1 gene which plays a central role in cilia formation.

name: Opitz-GBBB syndrome
description: A monogenic disease that is characterized by hypertelorism, hypospadias, and additional midline defects resulting from mutations to the MID1 gene in the X-linked form or from a deletion on chromosome 22q11.2 in the autosomal dominant form.

name: Ogden syndrome
description: An X-linked disease resulting from a deficiency in N-terminal acetyltransferase, characterized by postnatal growth failure with severe delays and dysmorphic features in boys.

name: Zollinger-Ellison syndrome
description: A syndrome that is haracterized by the development of a one or more tumors (gastrinoma) in the pancreas, duodenum, or both that secrete excessive levels of gastrin, a hormone that stimulates production of acid by the stomach.

name: secondary progressive multiple sclerosis
description: A multiple sclerosis that is characterised by a worsening of disability, rather than by relapses followed by recovery, which progressively worsens until a steady progression of disability replaces the cycles of attacks.

name: primary progressive multiple sclerosis
description: A multiple sclerosis that is characterized by steady worsening of neurologic functioning, without any distinct relapses or periods of remission. The rate of progression may vary over time, with occasional plateaus or temporary improvements, but the progression is continuous.

name: progressive relapsing multiple sclerosis
description: A multiple sclerosis that is characterized by steadily worsening symptoms and attacks during periods of remission with disease progression from the onset.

name: iridogoniodysgenesis syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by the iris stroma being hypoplastic resulting from abnormalities in the differentiation of the anterior segment structures and increased values of intraocular pressure and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutations in the PITX2 gene.

name: juvenile polyposis syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by predisposition to hamartomatous benign polyps in the gastrointestinal tract, specifically in the stomach, small intestine, colon, and rectum.

name: proximal symphalangism
description: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by ankylosis of the proximal interphalangeal joints, carpal and tarsal bone fusion, and conductive deafness.

name: tarsal-carpal coalition syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by fusion of the carpals, tarsals, and phalanges, short first metacarpals causing brachydactyly; and humeroradial fusion.

name: fibular hypoplasia and complex brachydactyly
description: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterised by severe reduction or absence of the fibula and complex brachydactyly.

name: persistent Mullerian duct syndrome
description: A pseudohermaphroditism that is characterized by the persistence of Mullerian duct derivatives (i.e. uterus, cervix, fallopian tubes and upper two thirds of vagina) in a phenotypically and karyotypically male.

name: multiple cutaneous and mucosal venous malformations
description: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by multiple bluish cutaneous or mucosal venous lesions.

name: short QT syndrome
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by heart arrhythmia defined as a short QT interval on an EKG (less than 300 ms) that does not significantly change with heart rate, tall and peaked T waves, and a structurally normal heart.

name: multiple synostoses syndrome
description: A dysostosis that is characterized by premature joint ankylosis and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inhertitance.

name: cone dystrophy
description: A retinal disease that is characterized by the loss of cone cells, the photoreceptors responsible for both central and color vision.

name: achalasia microcephaly syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by microcephaly, intellectual deficit and early onset symptoms of achalasia (abnormal enlargement of the esophagus, impaired peristalsis, cardiospasm, recurrent vomiting and respiratory infections).

name: peroxisomal acyl-CoA oxidase deficiency
description: A peroxisomal disease that is characterized by hypotonia and seizures in the neonatal period and neurological regression in early infancy.

name: Ehlers-Danlos syndrome progeroid type
description: An Ehlers-Danlos syndrome that is characterized by aged appearance, developmental delay, short stature, craniofacial disproportion, generalized osteopenia, defective wound healing, hypermobile joints, hypotonic muscles, and loose but elastic skin and has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the B3GALT6 gene.

name: glioblastoma classical subtype
description: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by abnormally high levels of epidermal growth factor receptor and the absence of p53 mutations.

name: glioblastoma proneural subtype
description: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by IDH1 and p53 mutations and Platelet Derived Growth Factor A amplification.

name: glioblastoma mesenchymal subtype
description: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by the most frequent number of mutation of the Neurofibromin 1 gene.

name: glioblastoma neural subtype
description: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by the expression of several gene types that are also typical of the brain's normal, noncancerous nerve cells, or neurons.

name: Kahrizi syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by mental retardation, cataracts, coloboma, kyphosis, and coarse facial features and has_material_basis_in mutation in the SRD5A3 gene.

name: mucopolysaccharidosis IX
description: A mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency in hyaluronidase.

name: biotin deficiency
description: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by thinning of the hair (often with loss of hair color), and red scaly rash around the eyes, nose, and mouth.

name: congenital adrenal hyperplasia
description: A steroid inherited metabolic disorder that is characterized by adrenal insufficiency and variable degrees of hyper or hypo androgeny manifestations resulting from steroidogenic enzyme deficiency.

name: spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia, Pakistani type
description: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that is characterized by short stature, short and bowed lower limbs, mild brachydactyly, kyphoscoliosis, abnormal gait, enlarged knee joints, precocious osteoarthropathy, and normal intelligence.

name: spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia with congenital joint dislocations
description: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that is characterized by short stature of prenatal onset, joint dislocations (knees, hips, radial heads), club feet, and limitation of range of motion that can involve all large joints.

name: temtamy preaxial brachydactyly syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by brachydactyly, hyperphalangism of digits, facial dysmorphism, dental anomalies, sensorineural hearing loss, delayed motor and mental development, and growth retardation and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the CHSY1 gene.

name: eye adnexa disease
description: An eye and adnexa disease that is located_in the adnexa of the eye.

name: urofacial syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by inverted facial expressions in association with a severe and early-onset form of dysfunctional urinary voiding.

name: Stargardt disease
description: An age related macular degeneration that is characterized by progressive vision loss usually to the point of legal blindness.

name: transcobalamin II deficiency
description: A vitamin B12 deficiency that is characterized by a lack of vitamin B12 intestinal absorption resulting from a deficiency in the B12 transport protein TCII.

name: Matthew-Wood syndrome
description: An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by microphthalmia or anophthalmia, pulmonary agenesis, and diaphragmatic defect.

name: atrioventricular block
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by the impairment of the conduction between the atria and ventricles of the heart.

name: sinoatrial node disease
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by dysfunction of the impulse-generating (pacemaker) tissue located in the right atrium of the heart which generates normal sinus rhythm.

name: endocardium disease
description: A heart disease that is located_in the innermost layer of tissue that lines the chambers of the heart.

name: rheumatic heart disease
description: A heart valve disease that is characterized by repeated inflammation with fibrinous repair. The cardinal anatomic changes of the valve include leaflet thickening, commissural fusion, and shortening and thickening of the tendinous cords.It is caused by an autoimmune reaction to Group A beta-hemolytic streptococci (GAS) that results in valvular damage.

name: artery disease
description: A vascular disease that is located_in an artery.

name: pericardium disease
description: A cardiovascular system disease that is located_in the  fibrous sac surrounding the heart.

name: peripheral artery disease
description: An artery disease that is characterized by build up of plaque in the arteries that carry blood to your head, organs, and limbs.

name: familial encephalopathy with neuroserpin inclusion bodies
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by intraneuronal inclusions of mutant neuroserpin resulting in progressive encephalopathy, dementia and seizures and has_material_basis_in a mutation in the SERPINI1 gene inherited in an in autosomal dominant pattern.

name: pyrimidine metabolic disorder
description: An inherited metabolic disorder involving dysfunction of pyrimidine metabolism.

name: orotic aciduria
description: A pyrimidine metabolic disorder that is characterized by an excessive secretion of orotic acid in urine.

name: CHARGE syndrome
description: A syndrome that is acterized by a pattern of congenital anomalies including choanal atresia and malformations of the heart, inner ear, and retina.

name: generalized dystonia
description: A dystonia that affects most or all of the body.

name: focal dystonia
description: A dystonia that is localized to a specific part of the body.

name: multifocal dystonia
description: A dystonia that involves two or more unrelated body parts.

name: segmental dystonia
description: A dystonia that affects two or more adjacent parts of the body.

name: cervical dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized by simultaneous contraction of the agonist and antagonist muscles that control the position of the head contracting during dystonic movement which causes the neck to involuntarily turn to the left, right, upwards, and/or downwards.

name: focal hand dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that affects a single muscle or small group of muscles in the hand resulting from involuntary muscular contractions.

name: oculogyric crisis
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized by a prolonged involuntary upward deviation of the eyes.

name: oromandibular dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized by distortions of the mouth and tongue.

name: spasmodic dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that involves the muscles that control the vocal cords, resulting in strained or breathy speech.

name: cranio-facial dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized as dystonia that affects the muscles of the head, face, and neck.

name: hemidystonia
description: A multifocal dystonia that involves the arm and leg on the same side of the body.

name: sleep apnea
description: A sleep disorder characterized by repeated cessation and commencing of breathing that repeatedly disrupts sleep.

name: obstructive sleep apnea
description: A sleep apnea that is characterized by repeated collapse and obstruction of the upper airway during sleep, which results in reduced airflow (hypopnea) or complete airflow cessation (apnea), oxygen desaturation, and arousals from sleep.

name: diabetic encephalopathy
description: A brain disease that is characterized by functional impairment of cognition, cerebral signal conduction, neurotransmission and synaptic plasticity, and underlying structural pathology associated with diabetes.

name: glomerulosclerosis
description: A glomerulonephritis that is characterized by hardening of the glomerulus in the kidney.

name: Perrault syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disesase that is characterized by sensorineural hearing loss and ovarian failure.

name: Marshall-Smith syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by advanced bone age, failure to thrive, respiratory problems, dysmorphic facial features, and variable mental retardation.

name: colorectal adenocarcinoma
description: A colorectal cancer that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: tongue squamous cell carcinoma
description: A head and neck squamous cell carcinoma that is located_in the tongue.

name: oral squamous cell carcinoma
description: An oral cavity cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: Jensen syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by sensorineural hearing loss with onset in infancy, followed in adolescence by progressive optic nerve atrophy with loss of vision and in adulthood by progressive dementia.

name: in situ pulmonary adenocarcinoma
description: A lung cancer that derives_from the distal bronchioles or alveoli that initially exhibit a specific non-invasive growth pattern.

name: follicular lymphoma
description: A B-cell lymphoma that is characterized as an indolent non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and has_material_basis_in follicle center B-cells (centrocytes and centroblasts).

name: Caroli disease
description: A bile duct disease that is characterized by abnormal dilatation of the intrahepatic bile ducts.

name: pancreatic agenesis
description: A pancreas disease that is characterized by the failure of the pancreas to develop prior to birth.

name: fragile X-associated tremor/ataxia syndrome
description: A X-linked hereditary ataxia that is characterized by adult-onset progressive intention tremor and gait ataxia, has_material_basis_in expanded trinucleotide repeat of the FMR1 gene that results_in a toxic gain of function of FMR1 RNA.

name: Koolen de Vries syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by developmental delay, intellectual disability, muscle weakness (hypotonia), epilepsy, distinctive facial features and congenital malformations of the heart, urogenital tract and the central nervous system, and has_physical_basis_in either a chromosome 17 (17q21.31) microdeletion or a mutation in the KANSL1-gene.

name: inclusion body myopathy with Paget disease of bone and frontotemporal dementia
description: A syndrome that is characterized by progressive proximal muscle weakness, steolytic bone lesions consistent with Paget disease, and frontotemporal dementia and has_physical_basis_in mutation in the valosin containing protein (VCP).

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 5
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by the early-onset of cerebellar signs and eye movement abnormalities with a very slow disease progression, and has material basis in mutation in the SPTBN2 gene.

name: infantile cerebellar-retinal degeneration
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by onset between ages 2 and 6 months of truncal hypotonia, athetosis, seizures, and ophthalmologic abnormalities, particularly optic atrophy and retinal degeneration.

name: triosephosphate isomerase deficiency
description: A glucose metabolism disorder that is characterized by chronic haemolytic anaemia, cardiomyopathy, susceptibility to infections and severe neurological dysfunction, and has_physical_basis_in the triosephosphate isomerase enzyme (TPI1) gene inherited as an autosomal recessive trait.

name: IMAGe syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by intrauterine growth restriction, metaphyseal dysplasia, adrenal hypoplasia congenita, genital abnormalities and has_physical_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the CDKN1C gene.

name: Troyer syndrome
description: A hereditary spastic paraplegia that is characterized by spasticity of the leg muscles, progressive muscle weakness, paraplegia, muscle wasting in the hands and feet (distal amyotrophy), small stature, developmental delay, learning disorders, speech difficulties (dysarthria), and mood swings, and has_material_basis_in a mutation of the SPG20 gene.

name: Townes-Brocks syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by imperforate anus, dysplastic ears often associated with sensorineural and/or conductive hearing impairment, and thumb malformations.

name: syndromic intellectual disability
description: An intellectual disability that is characterized by the presence of associated medical and behavioral sign and symptoms.

name: non-syndromic intellectual disability
description: An intellectual disability that is characterized by the absence of associated medical and behavioral signs and symptoms.

name: synucleinopathy
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by the abnormal accumulation of aggregates of alpha-synuclein protein in neurons, nerve fibres or glial cells.

name: adrenal cortical adenoma
description: An adrenal adenoma that is a benign tumor of the adrenal cortex.

name: adrenal gland pheochromocytoma
description: An adrenal medulla cancer that is characterized by overproduction of adrenaline.

name: gallbladder adenoma
description: A biliary tract neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin located_in the gallbladder.

name: ameloblastoma
description: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in odontogenic epithelium.

name: bone ameloblastoma
description: A bone benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in odontogenic epithelium and is located_in bone.

name: bone squamous cell carcinoma
description: A bone carcinoma that derives_from squamous epithelial cells.

name: bone chondrosarcoma
description: A chondrosarcoma that is located_in bone.

name: phalanx chondroma
description: A bone benign neoplasm that is located_in the phalanx that has_material_basis_in cartilaginous cells.

name: brain stem medulloblastoma
description: A brain stem cancer that begins in the lower part of the brain on the floor of the skull.

name: sacrum chordoma
description: A spinal chordoma that is located_in the sacrum.

name: corpus callosum oligodendroglioma
description: A brain oligodendroglioma located_in the corpus callosum.

name: medulloblastoma
description: An infratentorial cancer that is located_in the lower part of the brain and is a type of primitive neuroectodermal tumor.

name: parietal lobe ependymoma
description: A parietal lobe neoplasm that has_material_basis_in cells lining the ventricles of the brain.

name: salivary gland carcinoma
description: A salivary gland cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: inflammatory myofibroblastic tumor
description: A mesenchymal cell neoplasm that has_material_basis_in myofibroblastic cells admixed with inflammatory cells.

name: conjunctival nevus
description: A sensory organ benign neoplasm that is located in the eye conjunctiva.

name: mixed extragonadal germ cell cancer
description: A mixed germ cell cancer that is located_in areas of the body other than the ovary or testicle.

name: myelodysplastic syndrome
description: A bone marrow cancer that is characterized by under production of white blood cells, red blood cells and platelets.

name: MALT lymphoma
description: A non-Hodgkin lymphoma that has_material_basis_in mucosal tissue involved in antibody production.

name: cecum adenoma
description: A cecal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: appendix carcinoid tumor
description: An appendix cancer that has_material_basis_in neurodendocrine cells.

name: colon adenoma
description: A colonic benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: large intestine adenocarcinoma
description: A large intestine cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: large intestine adenoma
description: An intestinal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin and is located_in the large intestine.

name: rectum adenoma
description: An intestinal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin and is located_in the rectum.

name: bronchus mucoepidermoid carcinoma
description: A bronchus cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells, mucus-secreting cells, and intermediate cells.

name: lung combined type small cell adenocarcinoma
description: A lung combined type small cell carcinoma that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin.

name: vaginal carcinoma
description: A vaginal cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: trachea mucoepidermoid carcinoma
description: A trachea carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of squamous cells, mucus-secreting cells, and intermediate cells.

name: tonsil squamous cell carcinoma
description: A tonsil cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: pharynx squamous cell carcinoma
description: A pharynx cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: gastrointestinal carcinoma
description: A gastrointestinal system cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: spindle epithelial tumor with thymus-like differentiation tumor
description: A thyroid carcinoma that has_material_basis_in compact bundles of long spindle epithelial cells that merge with tubulopapillary structures and/or mucinous glands.

name: striated muscle rhabdoid tumor
description: A muscle cancer that is located_in striated muscle and has_material_basis_in rhabdoid cells which are large cells with eccentrically located nuclei and abundant, eosinophilic cytoplasm.

name: small intestine carcinoid neuroendocrine tumor
description: A small intestine cancer that has_material_basis_in cells of the neuroendocrine system.

name: jejunal adenocarcinoma
description: A jejunal cancer that is located_in the jejunum and has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue that has glandular origin.

name: duodenum adenoma
description: A duodenal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: ovarian melanoma
description: An ovarian cancer that has_material_basis_in melanoctyes.

name: mucosal melanoma
description: A melanoma that has_material_basis_in melanocytes located_in mucosal membranes lining the respiratory, gastrointestinal and urogenital tract.

name: sublingual gland adenoid cystic carcinoma
description: A sublingual gland cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures within the affected organ.

name: parotid gland adenoid cystic carcinoma
description: A parotid gland cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures within the affected organ.

name: lung mucoepidermoid carcinoma
description: A lung carcinoma that has_material_basis in a combination of squamous cells, mucus secreting cells and intermediate cells.

name: ovarian serous carcinoma
description: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in the lining of the ovary and produces a serum-like fluid.

name: ovarian clear cell carcinoma
description: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in cells with clear cytoplasm and glycogen secreting hob nail cells.

name: cervical neuroblastoma
description: An extracranial neuroblastoma that has_material_basis_in immature nerve cells.

name: extra-adrenal pheochromocytoma
description: An adrenal medulla cancer that originate in the ganglia of the sympathetic nervous system and are named based upon the primary anatomical site of origin.

name: retroperitoneal neuroblastoma
description: A retroperitoneal cancer that has_material_basis_in immature nerve cells.

name: breast lobular carcinoma
description: A breast carcinoma that derives_from breast lobules (milk glands).

name: uterine corpus endometrial carcinoma
description: A uterine corpus cancer that is derives_from the inner lining of the uterus.

name: endocervical adenocarcinoma
description: An endocervical carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: hereditary hypophosphatemic rickets with hypercalciuria
description: A rickets that has_material_basis_in increased serum 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D levels and increased intestinal calcium absorption and is characterized by the presence of hypophosphatemia secondary to renal phosphate wasting, radiographic and/or histologic evidence of rickets, limb deformities, muscle weakness, and bone pain.

name: autosomal dominant hypophosphatemic rickets
description: A rickets characterized by low levels of serum phosphate and elevated levels of ALP and phosphaturia and that has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: autosomal recessive hypophosphatemic rickets
description: A rickets that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance mutation in the DMP1 gene and is characterized by hypophosphatemia, rickets and/or osteomalacia and slow growth.

name: autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia
description: A hereditary ataxia that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: hereditary ataxia
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by slowly progressive incoordination of gait and often associated with poor coordination of hands, speech, and eye movements.

name: autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia, deafness and narcolepsy
cerebellar ataxia, mental retardation and dysequlibrium syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by congenital onset of nonprogressive cerebellar ataxia, disturbed equilibrium, and mental retardation, associated with cerebellar hypoplasia.

name: nonprogressive cerebellar atxia with mental retardation
infective endocarditis
description: An endocarditis that is characterized by inflammation of the endocardium caused by infectious agents.

name: withdrawal disorder
description: A substance-related disorder that occurs upon the abrupt discontinuation/separation or a decrease in dosage of the intake of medications, recreational drugs, and alcohol.

name: C1 inhibitor deficiency
description: A complement deficiency that is a functional deficiency in the complement component C1 inhibitor leading to hereditary angioedema (HAE) involving swelling due to leakage of fluid from blood vessels into connective tissue.

name: autoimmune disease of central nervous system
description: An autoimmune disease of the central nervous system.

name: autoimmune disease of endocrine system
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system resulting in production of antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the endocrine system.

name: artemis deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is caused when the DCLREI1, DNA cross-link repair 1C gene contains mutations resulting in the inability to repair DNA.

name: CD3zeta deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that affects the development and function of T cells.

name: Omenn syndrome
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that has_material_basis in the RAG1 and RAG2 genes on chromosome 11p and the Artemis gene on chromosome 10p. It is characterized by erythroderma, desquamation, alopecia, chronic diarrhea, failure to thrive, lymphadenopathy, and hepatosplenomegaly.

name: recombinase activating gene 1 deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on Chromosome 6 RAG1 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the T- and B-lymphocyte receptor genes.

name: recombinase activating gene 2 deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on Chromosome 6 RAG2 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the T- and B-lymphocyte receptor genes.

name: gamma chain deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is a X-linked SCID that has material basis in mutations in genes encoding common gamma chain proteins shared by the interleukin (IL-2,4,7,9,16 and21) receptors resulting in a non-functional gamma chain, defective interleukin signalling, minimal or ascent T- and NK cells and non-functional B-cells.

name: CD45 deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is an autosomal recessive disease with T and B lymphocyte dysfunction, due to a large deletion at one allelle and a point mutation at the other. The point mutation resulted in the alteration of intervening sequence 13 donor splice site. The population of T lymphocytes is diminished and unresponsive to mitogen stimulation. The level of B lymphocyte numbers, serum immunoglobulin decreased with age.

name: interleukin-7 receptor alpha deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that results from defective IL7R expression causes T-B+NK+ SCID. Loss of IL-7R function leads to the loss of an antiapoptotic signal, resulting in a loss of T-cell selection in thymus.

name: CD3delta deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by the absence of T cells but normal numbers of B cells. CD3D is essential for T cell development.

name: CD3epsilon deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is an autosomal recessive immunodeficiency that has material basis in mutations in the gene coding for T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3epsilon chain precursors. Patients with CD3epsilon deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the T-cell receptor CD3-complex.

name: CD3gamma deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency an autosomal recessive immunodeficiency that has material basis in mutations in the gene coding for T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3gamma chain precursors. Patients with CD3gamma deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the T-cell receptor CD3-complex. Affected patients have decreased T-cell numbers and function; B cells are variably affected.

name: coronin-1A deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is an actin regulator when mutated results in SCID through inhibition of thymic egress of mature thymocytes into peripheral lymphoid organs.

name: reticular dysgenesis
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the most severe form of SCID and has material basis in mutations in the gene encoding mitochondrial adenylate kinase 2. It is characterized by congenital agranulocytosis, lymphopenia, and lymphoid and thymic hypoplasia with absent cellular and humoral immunity functions.

name: DNA ligase IV deficiency
description: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that has material basis in a mutation in the LIG4 gene, a DNA ligase, encoding a protein essential for V(D)J recombination and DNA double-strand break (DSB) repair through nonhomologous end joining (NHEJ). Patients present with immunodeficiency and developmental and growth delay.

name: CD40 ligand deficiency
description: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that is a X-linked immunodeficiency with hyperimmunoglobulin M (XHIM) affecting isotype switching and is caused by the absence of CD40 ligand which is normally expressed on activated CD4+ T cells. Individuals with this mutation are unable to switch from IgM to IgG, IgA and IgE.

name: CD40 deficiency
description: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that has material basis in mutation in the TNFRSF5 gene, resulting in type 3 hyper-IgM immunodeficiency characterized by an inability of B cells to undergo isotype switching, an inability to mount an antibody-specific immune response, and a lack of germinal center formation.

name: lambda 5 deficiency
description: A B cell deficiency that has material basis in mutations in the IGLL1 gene. Lambda 5 mutations an cause a block in B cell development at the transition between the pro-B cell and the pre-B cell stage.

name: immunoglobulin alpha deficiency
description: A B cell deficiency that is an autosomal recessive disorder that has material basis in mutation in the IgA (CD79 alpha) antigen receptor.

name: B cell linker protein deficiency
description: A hypobammaglobulinemia that is a B cell deficiency that has material basis in a mutation in a cytoplasmic linker or adaptor protein that plays a critical role in B cell development, the B cell linker protein (BLNK) gene. Mutations in this gene cause hypoglobulinemia and absent B cells, a disease in which the pro- to pre-B-cell transition is developmentally blocked. The BLNK gene is associated with intracellular calcium mobilization, essential for cell activation.

name: Good syndrome
description: An agammaglobulinemia that is a condition where there is co-occurrence of deficient cell-mediated immunity and benign thymoma.

name: autoimmune disease of exocrine system
description: An immune system disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the exocrine system.

name: autoimmune disease of eyes, ear, nose and throat
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease of the eyes, ears, nose and throat.

name: autoimmune disease of gastrointestinal tract
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the gastrointestinal tract.

name: autoimmune disease of musculoskeletal system
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the musculoskeletal system.

name: autoimmune disease of peripheral nervous system
description: An autoimmune disease of the nervous system that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the peripheral nervous system.

name: intrinsic cardiomyopathy
description: A cardiomyopathy that is characterized as weakness in the muscle of the heart that is not due to an identifiable external cause.

name: developmental disorder of mental health
description: A disease of mental health that occur during a child's developmental period between birth and age 18 resulting in retarding of the child's psychological or physical development.

name: specific developmental disorder
description: A developmental disorder of mental health that categorizes specific learning disabilities and developmental disorders affecting coordination.

name: autoimmune disease of skin and connective tissue
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the skin and connective tissue.

name: pervasive developmental disorder
description: A developmental disorder of mental health that refers to a group of five disorders characterized by impairments in socialization and communication, as well as restricted interests and repetitive behaviors.

name: autism spectrum disorder
description: A pervasive developmental disorder that is a spectrum of psychological conditions. The disease has_symptom widespread abnormalities of social interactions and communication, has_symptom severely restricted interests and has_symptom highly repetitive behavior.

name: atypical autism
description: An autism spectrum disorder that involves some autistic symptoms occuring after age 3 with an abscence of all the traits necessary for a diagnosis of autism.

name: sexual disorder
description: A disease of mental health that involves the impairment in normal sexual functioning.

name: Munchausen by proxy
description: A factitious disorder that involves a care giver's deliberate exaggeration, fabrication, and/or induce physical, psychological, behavioral, and/or mental health problems in others.

name: aphasia
description: A language disorder that involves an acquired impairment of any laguage modality such as producting or comprehending spoken or written language.

name: writing disorder
description: A learning disability that involves impaired written language ability such as impairments in handwriting, spelling, organization of ideas, and composition.

name: nosophobia
description: A specific phobia that involves an irrational fear of contracting a disease.

name: autoimmune disease of urogenital tract
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the urogenital tract.

name: autoimmune disease of blood
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the blood.

name: autoimmune disease of cardiovascular system
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the cardiovascular system.

name: popliteal pterygium syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by abnormal development of the face, skin and genitals. Clinical expressions of the disease include cleft lip, with or without cleft palate, contractures of the lower extremities, abnormal external genitalia, syndactyly of fingers and/or toes, and a pyramidal skin fold over the hallux nail. It has material basis in mutations in the IRF6 gene on chromosome 1.

name: hypersensitivity reaction disease
description: An immune system disease that has material basis in abnormal immune responses.

name: lymphoma
description: A hematologic cancer that affects lymphocytes that reside in the lymphatic system and in blood-forming organs.

name: non-Hodgkin lymphoma
description: A lymphoma that is characterized as any kind of lymphoma except Hodgkin's lymphoma.

name: cutaneous T cell lymphoma
description: A non-Hodgkin's lymphoma that has material basis in a mutation of T cells.

name: familial juvenile hyperuricemic nephropathy
description: A kidney disease that is characterized by hyperuricemia with renal uric acid under-excretion, gout and chronic kidney disease.

name: Pearson syndrome
description: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by sideroblastic anemia and exocrine pancreas dysfunction.

name: marantic endocarditis
description: An endocarditis that results from the deposition of small sterile vegetations on valve leaflets.

name: pre-malignant neoplasm
description: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body, which do not invade or destroy the surrounding tissue but, given enough time, will transform into a cancer.

name: benign neoplasm
description: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body which lack the ability to metastasize.

name: lymphatic system cancer
description: An immune system cancer that is located_in the lymphatic system and is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of lymphoid tissue.

name: immune system cancer
description: An organ system cancer located_in the immune system that is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation in organs of the immune system.

name: cell type benign neoplasm
description: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the type of cell or tissue from which it is derived.

name: organ system benign neoplasm
description: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the organ system from which it is arising from.

name: endocrine organ benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in endocrine glands which secretes a type of hormone directly into the bloodstream to regulate the body.

name: central nervous system organ benign neoplasm
cardiovascular organ benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm disease located_in the blood, heart, blood vessels or the lymphatic system.

name: immune system organ benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the immune system organs.

name: bone benign neoplasm
description: A connective tissue benign neoplasm that is located_in bone.

name: sensory organ benign neoplasm
description: A nervous system benign neoplasm that is located_in a sensory organ.

name: thoracic benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplam that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

name: musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the muscular and skeletal organs.

name: musculoskeletal system cancer
description: An organ system cancer located_in the muscular and skeletal organs and characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of the musculoskeletal organs.

name: benign glioma
description: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

name: central nervous system primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm
cerebellar medulloblastoma
description: A cerebellum cancer that begins in the lower part of the brain on the floor of the skull.

name: brain glioma
description: A brain cancer that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

name: nervous system benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the central nervous system or located_in the peripheral nervous system.

name: sensory system cancer
description: A nervous system cancer that is located_in the sensory system.

name: peritoneal benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the serous membrane lining the abdominal cavity or coelom.

name: thoracic disease
description: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

name: pharynx cancer
description: A gastrointestinal system cancer that is located_in the pharynx.

name: integumentary system benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the integumentary system organs.

name: integumentary system cancer
description: An organ system cancer that is located_in the skin, hair and nails.

name: connective tissue benign neoplasm
description: A musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm that is located_in connective tissue.

name: heavy chain disease
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type IV disease that results from a proliferation of cells producing immunoglobulin heavy chains.

name: alpha chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of alpha antibodies (IgA).

name: gamma heavy chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of gamma antibody (IgG).

name: mu chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of mu antibody (IgM).

name: delta chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of delta antibody (IgD).

name: akinetopsia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of motion perception.

name: alexithymia
description: An agnosia that is a deficiency in understanding, processing, or describing emotions.

name: amusia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize musical notes, rhythms, and intervals.

name: anosognosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to gain feedback about one's own condition or impairments.

name: apperceptive agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish visual shapes.

name: apraxia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to map out physical actions in order to repeat them in functional activities.

name: associative agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize visual scenes or classes of objects but retain the abilty to describe them.

name: auditory agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguishing environmental and non-verbal auditory cues including difficulty distinguishing speech from non-speech sounds even though hearing is usually normal.

name: autotopagnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to orient parts of the body.

name: color agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize a color, while being able to perceive or distinguish it.

name: cortical deafness
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive any auditory information but whose hearing is intact.

name: finger agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish the fingers on the hand.

name: form agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive a whole object while perceiving only parts of details.

name: integrative agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to integrate these elements together into comprehensible perceptual wholes while recognizing elements of the whole.

name: mirror agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to acknowledge objects in the neglected field that are visible when a mirror reflects the object visible in the non-neglected field.

name: pain agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive and process pain.

name: phonagnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize familiar voices.

name: semantic agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognise an object while maintaining the use of non-visual sensory systems such as feeling, tapping, smelling, rocking or flicking the object to recognise the object.

name: simultanagnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recgonize a whole image or scene while retianing the ability to recognize objects or details in their visual field one at a time.

name: social emotional agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive facial expression, body language and intonation, rendering them unable to non-verbally perceive people's emotions and limiting that aspect of social interaction.

name: astereognosia
description: An agnosia that is the loss of the ability to recognize objects by touch based on its texture, size and weight.

name: tactile agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize or identify objects by touch alone.

name: time agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehend the succession and duration of events.

name: topographical agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to rely on visual cues to guide them directionally due to the inability to recognise objects.

name: verbal auditory agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognising spoken words as semantically meaningful.

name: visual agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognize objects.

name: visual verbal agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehending the meaning of written words.

name: diffuse alopecia areata
description: An alopecia areata that involves diffuse loss of hair over the whole scalp.

name: acquired metabolic disease
description: A disease of metabolism that has _material_basis_in enzyme deficiency or accumulation of enzymes or toxins which interfere with normal function due to an endocrine organ disease, organ malfunction, inadequate intake, dietary deficiency, or malabsorption.

name: organic acidemia
description: An amino acid metabolic disorder that disrupts normal amino acid metabolism causing a building up of branched-chain amino acids.

name: survival motor neuron spinal muscular atrophy
description: A spinal muscular atrophy that is associated with the survival of motor neuron protein.

name: Kennedy's disease
description: A spinal muscular dystrophy that has_material_basis_in an X-linked recessive expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) in exon 1 of AR gene encoding the androgen receptor.

name: dentatorubral-pallidoluysian atrophy
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that has_material_basis_in expansion of  CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) encoding a polyglutamine tract in the atrophin-1 protein.

name: body dysmorphic disorder
description: A somatoform disorder that involves an excessive concern about and preoccupation with a perceived defect in his or her physical features (body image).

name: pain disorder
description: A somatoform disorder that involves chronic pain in one or more areas, and is thought to be caused by psychological stress.

name: Kleine-Levin syndrome
description: A recurrent hypersomnia that is characterized by recurring periods of excessive amounts of sleep and altered behavior.

name: bipolar ll disorder
description: A bipolar disorder that is characterized by at least one hypomanic episode and at least one major depressive episode; with this disorder, depressive episodes are more frequent and more intense than manic episodes.

name: seasonal affective disorder
description: A mental depression that involves presentation of depressive symptoms only during a specific season of the year.

name: histidinemia
description: A histidine metabolism disease that involves a deficiency of the enzyme histidase.

name: benign familial infantile epilepsy
description: An infancy electroclinical syndrome that is characterized by convulsions, with onset at age 3 to 12 months.

name: generalized epilepsy with febrile seizures plus
description: An idiopathic generalized epilepsy that is characterized by febrile seizures often with accessory afebrile generalized tonic-clonic seizures with childhood onset.

name: Dravet syndrome
description: An epilepsy that is characterized by frequent febrile seizures with onset before 1 year.

name: juvenile absence epilepsy
description: An adolescence-adult electroclinical syndrome statring between the age of ten to 17 years characterized by the occurrence of typical absence seizures.

name: Timothy syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by cardiac, hand/foot, facial, and neurodevelopmental features. The two forms are type 1 (classic) and type 2, a rare form that has_material_basis_in mutations in a transcript variant of CACNA1C on chromosome 12p13.33.

name: GABA aminotransferase deficiency
description: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by a defect in the gene coding for gamma-aminobutyrate transaminase, which is responsible for catabolism of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), an important, mostly inhibitory neurotransmitter in the central nervous system, into succinic semialdehyde.

name: succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase deficiency
description: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by a deficiency of succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase resulting in elevated levels of gamma-hydroxybutyric acid.

name: gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder
description: An amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by impairment of the GABA catabolic pathway.

name: homocarnosinosis
description: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by an excess of homocarnosine in the brain and has_material_basis_in a deficiency of serum carnosinase in its ability to hydrolyze homocarnosine.

name: familial hemiplegic migraine
description: A migraine with aura that is characterized by temporary numbness or weakness, often affecting one side of the body (hemiparesis). Additional features of an aura can include difficulty with speech, confusion, and drowsiness.

name: Renpenning syndrome
description: An intellectual disability that is characterized by small head size (microcephaly), long narrow face, short stature, small testes, and intellectual deficit which follows X-linked inheritance and presents most often in males.

name: colitis
description: An inflammatory bowel disease that involves inflammation located_in colon.

name: ischemic colitis
description: A colitis caused_by inadequate blood supply to the colon.

name: microscopic colitis
description: A colitis that can only be diagnosed_by the examination of colon tissue under a microscope.

name: collagenous colitis
description: A colitis characterized by a distinctive thickening of the subepithelial collagen table.

name: lymphocytic colitis
description: A colitis characterized by an accumulation of lymphocytes in the colonic epithelium and connective tissue (lamina propria).

name: Clostridium difficile colitis
description: A colitis characterized by an overgrowth of Clostridium difficile bacteria.

name: chemical colitis
description: A colitis caused_by introduction of various chemicals.

name: diversion colitis
description: A colitis caused_by diversion of the fecal stream due to complication of ileostomy or colostomy.

name: jejunoileitis
description: An inflammatory bowel disease that is characterized by patchy areas of inflammation located_in jejunum, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom cramps and has_symptom formation of fistulas.

name: ileitis
description: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in ileum, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom abdominal pain, often in the right lower quadrant, has_symptom weight loss.

name: ileocolitis
description: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in colon and located_in ileum, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom abdominal pain in middle or lower right part.

name: gastroduodenal Crohn's disease
description: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in stomach and located_in duodenum, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom weight loss and has_symptom loss of appetite.

name: Crohn's colitis
description: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in colon only, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom rectal bleeding, has_symptom skin lesions and has_symptom formation of ulcers, fistulas and abscesses around the anus.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 1
description: The most common type of familial ALS that has material basis in mutation in the SOD1 gene on chromosome 21.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 2
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the alsin gene on chromosome 2.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 3
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in loci on chromosome 18.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 4
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis with juvenile onset that has material basis in mutation in the SETX gene on chromosome 9.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 5
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the SPG11 gene on chromosome 15q21.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 6
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the FUS gene on chromosome 16.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 7
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in loci on chromosome 20.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 9
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the ANG gene on chromosome 14.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 10
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the TARDBP gene on chromosome 1.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 11
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the FIG4 gene on chromosome 6.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 12
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the OPTN gene on chromosome 10.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 13
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis where a mutation that has material basis in the ATXN2 gene on chromosome 12 contributes to suscepitbility.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 14
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the VCP gene on chromosome 9.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 15
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the UBQLN2 gene on chromosome X.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 16
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the SIGMAR1 gene (SETX) on chromosome 9.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 17
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the CHMP2B gene on chromosome 3.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 18
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the PFN1 gene on chromosome 17.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 19
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the ERBB4 gene on chromosome 2.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 20
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis with juvenile onset that has material basis in mutation in the HNRNPA1 gene on chromosome 12.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 21
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the MATR3 gene on chromosome 5.

name: FTDALS1
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the C9ORF72 gene on chromosome 9. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.

name: FTDALS2
description: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has material basis in mutation in the CHCHD10 gene on chromosome 22. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.

name: Balo concentric sclerosis
description: A demyelinating disease characterized by the fact that the demyelinated tissues form concentric layers.

name: Cogan syndrome
description: An eye disease characterized by nonsyphilitic interstitial keratitis located_in cornea, has_symptom fever, has_symptom fatigue.

name: Cogan-Reese syndrome
description: An eye disease characterized by variable iris atrophy, pigmented and pedunculated nodules located_in iris and attachment of the iris to the cornea (peripheral anterior synechiae) and characterized_by glaucoma.

name: CREST syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by calcinosis, Raynaud's phenomeno, esophageal dysmotility, sclerodactyly and telangiectasia.

name: lymph node adenoid cystic carcinoma
description: A lymph node cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures of the lymph nodes. These structures are typically filled with a mucous-like material or contain abnormal fibrous membranes.

name: physical urticaria
description: An urticaria induced by external physical influences.

name: Maffucci syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by the presence of multiple enchondromas (benign growths of cartilage) associated with multiple hemangiomas.

name: Scheie syndrome
description: A mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by corneal clouding, facial dysmorphism and normal lifespan.

name: agraphia
description: An acquired writing disorder causing a loss in the ability to communicate through writing, either due to some motor dysfunction or the inability to spell.

name: atrial fibrillation
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by uncoordinated electrical activity in the heart's upper chambers (the atria), which causes the heartbeat to become fast and irregular and has symptoms palpitations, weakness, fatigue, lightheadedness, dizziness, confusion, shortness of breath and chest pain.

name: 3MC syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by blepharophimosis, blepharoptosis, highly arched eyebrows hypertelorism, cleft lip and palate, postnatal growth deficiency, cognitive impairment, hearing loss and, in a smaller percentage of cases, craniosynostosis, radioulnar synostosis and genital and vesicorenal anomalies. It encompasses four disorders that were previously designated the Malpuech, Michels, Mingarelli and Carnevale syndromes.

name: acrofrontofacionasal dysostosis
description: A dysostosis characterized by intellectual disability, short stature, hypertelorism, broad notched nasal tip, cleft lip palate, postaxial camptobrachypolysyndactyly, fibular hypoplasia and anomalies of foot structure.

name: Adams-Oliver syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by defects of the scalp (aplasia cutis congenita), abnormalities of the fingers, toes, arms and legs.

name: intracranial berry aneurysm
description: An intracranial aneurysm with a characteristic rounded shape; the most common form of cerebral aneurysm.

name: Baraitser-Winter syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by distinctive facial features including hypertelorism, large eyelid openings, ptosis, high-arched eyebrows, a broad nasal bridge and tip of the nose, a long space between the nose and the upper lip, full cheeks and a pointed chin; structural abnormalities of the brain might also be present.

name: basal ganglia calcification
description: A basal ganglia disease characterized by the presence of abnormal calcium deposits of unknown cause in the brain; has symptom dementia, psychosis, mood swings and loss of acquired motor skills.

name: Bruck syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by a combination of multiple joint contractures and osteogenesis imperfecta.

name: branchiootic syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by malformations of the outer, middle and inner ear and branchial and renal malformations. Mutations of the EYA1, SIX1 and SIX5 genes are associated with the syndrome.

name: cardiofaciocutaneous syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by unusually sparse, brittle, curly hair, macrocephaly, a prominent forehead and bi-temporal narrowing, intellectual disability, failure to thrive, congenital heart defects, short stature and skin abnormalities; it is that has material basis in mutation in the BRAF, MAP2K1, MAP2kK2 and KRAS genes.

name: Carpenter syndrome
description: An acrocephalosyndactylia characterized by craniosynostosis, acrocephaly, obesity, syndactyly and polydactyly.

name: carnitine palmitoyltransferase II deficiency
description: A lipid metabolism disorder characterized by an enzymatic defect that prevents long-chain fatty acids from being transported into the mitochondria.

name: xanthinuria
description: A purine-pyrimidine metabolic disorder characterized by deficiency of xanthine oxidase, resulting in excretion of large amounts of xanthine in the urine and the formation of xanthine stones.

name: Warburg micro syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by severe intellectual disability, microcephaly, congenital cataract, microcornea, microphthalmia, agenesis or hypoplasia of the corpus callosum and hypogenitalism.

name: Van Maldergem syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by facial abnormalities such as telecanthus, epicanthus, broad flattened nose, large inverted W-shaped mouth and malformed ears, malformed extremities such as camptodactyly, clinodactyly, interdigital webbing and joint hyperlaxity and mental retardation.

name: Van der Woude syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by the combination of lower lip pits, cleft lip with or without cleft palate and cleft palate alone.

name: UV-sensitive syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by photosensitivity and liver spots (solar lentigines).

name: 3-M syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by dwarfism, facial dysmorphia and skeletal abnormalities.

name: synpolydactyly
description: A syndactyly characterized by an increased number of digits; often a result of a mutation in the HOX D13 gene.

name: stuttering
description: An articulation disorder characterized by involuntary sound repetition and disruption or blocking of speech.

name: specific language impairment
description: A language disorder characterized by difficulty in language acquisition despite otherwise normal development and in the absence of any obvious explanatory factors.

name: Mast syndrome
description: A hereditary spastic paraplegia associated with dementia.

name: MASA syndrome
description: A hereditary spastic paraplegia that is characterized by hydrocephalus, spasticity of the lower limbs, adducted thumbs, aphasia, seizures, agenesis of the corpus callosum and intellectual disability in the mild to moderate range.

name: Smith-McCort dysplasia
description: An osteochondrodysplasia characterized by short limbs and a short trunk with a barrel-shaped chest and has material basis in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DYM gene on chromosome 18q.

name: Simpson-Golabi-Behmel syndrome
description: An X-linked disease characterized by pre- and postnatal overgrowth and craniofacial, skeletal, cardiac and renal abnormalities.

name: scoliosis
description: A bone structure disease characterized by an appreciable lateral deviation in the normally straight vertical line of the spine.

name: idiopathic scoliosis
description: A scoliosis with no known cause.

name: sclerosteosis
description: A hyperostosis characterized by excessive bone formation most prominent in the skull, mandible, clavicle, ribs and diaphyses of long bones; bone formation occurs throughout life.

name: sclerocornea
description: A corneal disease in which the cornea blends with sclera, resulting in clouding of the cornea.

name: scapuloperoneal myopathy
description: A muscular dystrophy which begins at the lower legs and affects the shoulder region earlier and more severely than distal arm.

name: Robinow syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by mild to moderate short stature due to growth delays after birth, distinctive craniofacial abnormalities, skeletal malformations and genital abnormalities.

name: rippling muscle disease 2
description: A muscle tissue disease characterized by muscles unusually sensitive to movement or pressure; the proximal muscles are most affected, especially the thighs.

name: Dowling-Degos disease
description: A pigmentation disease characterized by a reticulate pattern of abnormally dark skin coloring, particularly in the body's folds and creases.

name: dyschromatosis symmetrica hereditaria
description: A pigmentation disease characterized by progressively pigmented and depigmented macules, often mixed in a reticulate pattern, concentrated on the dorsal extremities.

name: reticulate acropigmentation of Kitamura
description: A pigmentation disease characterized by lesions that initially arise as letiginous, hyperpigmented macules in a reticular pattern on the dorsal aspect of the hands and feet. Over time, lesions may spread proximally and may darken; palmoplantar pitting and dermatoglyphic disruption may also be present.

name: renal-hepatic-pancreatic dysplasia
description: A physical disorder characterized by pancreatic fibrosis, renal dysplasia and hepatic dysgenesis; it is usual fatal soon after birth.

name: ptosis
description: An eye disease characterized by the drooping or falling of the upper or lower eyelid.

name: congenital ptosis
description: A ptosis characterized by eyelid drop present at birth.

name: gallbladder disease
description: A gastrointestinal system disease that is located_in the gallbladder.

name: primary pigmented nodular adrenocortical disease
description: An adrenal cortex disease characterized by small to normal sized adrenal glands containing multiple small cortical pigmented nodules.

name: photosensitive epilepsy
description: An epilepsy characterized by seizures triggered by visual stimuli that form patterns in space or time, such as flashing lights.

name: Ohdo syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis, dental hypoplasia, hearing impairment and intellectual disability.

name: oculodentodigital dysplasia
description: A syndrome characterized by craniofacial, neurologic, limb and ocular abnormalities.

name: cold-induced sweating syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by problems with regulating body temperature and other abnormalities affecting many parts of the body. It has material basis in mutations in the CRLF1 gene.

name: congenital secretory chloride diarrhea 1
description: A secretory diarrhea that has material basis in mutation in the SLC26A3 gene.

name: dyschromatosis universalis hereditaria
description: A pigmentation disease characterized by reticulate hyper- and hypo-pigmentated macules in a generalized distribution.

name: megalocornea
description: A corneal disease characterized by a bilaterally enlarged corneal diameter without an increase in intraocular pressure. It has material basis in mutation in the CHRDL1 gene.

name: Meier-Gorlin syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disorder characterized by severe intrauterine and postnatal growth retardation, microcephaly, bilateral microtia and hypoplastic patellae.

name: autosomal dominant non-syndromic intellectual disability
description: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

name: autosomal recessive non-syndromic intellectual disability
description: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.

name: syndromic X-linked intellectual disability
description: A syndromic intellectual characterized by an X-linked inheritance pattern.

name: uvulitis
description: An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the swelling of the uvula to 3-5 times its normal size.

name: adenoid hypertrophy
description: An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the unusual growth of the adenoid tonsil; has_symptom snoring, has_symptom hyponasality, has_symptom otitis media with effusion, has symptom mouth breathing.

name: angular cheilitis
description: A cheilitis characterized by inflammation of one or both of the corners of the mouth.

name: tracheomalacia
description: A tracheal disease characterized by flaccidity of the tracheal support cartilage.

name: persistent generalized lymphadenopathy
description: A lymph node disease characterized by enlarged, non-painful lymph nodes occurring for more than three to six months for which no other reason can be found.

name: oral hairy leukoplakia
description: A mouth disease characterized by a white patch on the side of the tongue with a corrugated or hairy appearance; caused by Epstein-Barr virus.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome I
description: An orofaciodigital syndrome characterized by polycystic kidney disease and variable involvement of the central nervous system and has_material_basis_in X-linked inheritance of the OFD1 gene.

name: lung abscess
description: A lung disease characterized by microbial infection which causes a type of liquefactive necrosis of the pulmonary tissue and formation of cavities containing necrotic debris or fluid.

name: acute promyelocytic leukemia
description: An acute myeloid leukemia characterized by accumulation of promyelocytes in the bone marrow and by a translocation between chromosomes 15 and 17.

name: cardiac arrest
description: A congestive heart failure characterized by a sudden stop in effective blood circulation due to the failure of the heart to contract effectively or at all.

name: inguinal hernia
description: An intestinal disease characterized by a protrusion of abdominal cavity contests through the inguinal canal.

name: umbilical hernia
description: A intestinal disease characterized by the protrusion by part of the intestine though an opening in the abdominal muscles.

name: mastoiditis
description: A middle ear disease characterized by an inflammation of the mucosal lining of the mastoid antrum and the mastoid air cell system inside the mastoid process.

name: breast abscess
description: A breast disease characterized by a collection of pus in the breast.

name: dental abscess
description: A tooth disease characterized by a localized collection of pus associated with a tooth.

name: cervical polyp
description: A cervix disease characterized by a benign polyp on the surface of the cervical canal.

name: myelomeningocele
description: A spina bifida characterized by protrusion of the spinal cord through an opening, covered by meningeal membranes.

name: omphalocele
description: A physical disorder characterized by a defect in the development of the abdominal wall muscles, resulting in the intestines, liver and other organs to remain outside of the abdomen in a sac.

name: anal fistula
description: An anus disease characterized by is an abnormal connection between the epithelialised surface of the anal canal and the perianal skin.

name: ectopic pregnancy
description: A female reproductive system disease characterized by the implantation of the embryo outside the uterine cavity.

name: Rapp-Hodgkin syndrome
description: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by abnormal development of ectodermal tissues including the skin, hair, nails, teeth and sweat glands and anhidrotic ectodermal dysplasia with cleft lip/palate.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 2
description: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has material basis in mutation in the TMEM70 gene on chromosome 8q21.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 3
description: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has material basis in mutation in the ATP5E gene on chromosome 20q13.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 4
description: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has material basis in mutation in the ATP5A1 gene on chromosome 18q.

name: transient neonatal diabetes mellitus
description: A neonatal diabetes mellitus characterized by hyperglycemia during the neonatal period that remits during infancy but recurs in later life in most patients.

name: autosomal dominant sideroblastic anemia
description: A sideroblastic anemia characterized by an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria
description: An organic acidemia that is characterized by elevated levels of 3-methylglutaconic acid and 3-methylglutaric acid in the urine.

name: CEDNIK syndrome
description: An autosomal recessive disease that has material basis in homozygous mutation in the SNAP29 gene and characterized by a unique constellation of clinical manifestations including microcephaly, severe neurologic impairment, psychomotor retardation, failure to thrive, facial dysmoprhism, palmoplantar keratoderma and late-onset ichthyosis.

name: parameningeal embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma
description: An embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma located in the parameningeal region.

name: chronic atrial and intestinal dysrhythmia
description: A syndrome characterized by a unique combination of cardiac arrhythmias and intestinal pseudo-obstruction. It has material basis in the mutated SGOL1 protein. Distinctive clinical features include atrial dysrhythmias, sick sinus syndrome (SSS) and valve anomalies and chronic intestinal pseudo-obstruction (CIPO).

name: ciliopathy
description: A genetic disease associated with mutations encoding defective proteins, which result in either abnormal function formation or function of cilia.

name: agnathia-otocephaly complex
description: A physical disorder characterized by mandibular hypoplasia or agnathia, ventromedial auricular malposition (melotia) and/or auricular fusion (synotia), and microstomia with oroglossal hypoplasia or aglossia. Holoprosencephaly is the most commonly identified association, but skeletal, genitourinary and cardiovascular anomalies and situs inversus have been reported.

name: acromelic frontonasal dysostosis
description: A dysostosis characterized by cranium bifidum, severe hypertelorism, median cleft lip and palate, nasal bifurcation, brachycephaly, large fontanelle, tibial hemimelia, preaxial polydactyly of the feet and brain malformations.

name: glucocorticoid-induced osteoporosis
description: An osteoporosis caused by chronic glucocorticoid use. Glucocorticoids impair the replication, differentiation and function of osteoblasts and induce the apoptosis of mature osteoblasts and osteocytes; the also favor osteoclastogenesis leading to an increase in bone resorption.

name: acrodermatitis chronica atrophicans
description: An acrodermatitis characterized by a chronically progressive course, leading to widespread atrophy of the skin. It is a clinical manifestation of Lyme borreliosis.

name: bacillary angiomatosis
description: A bartonellosis that has_material_basis_in Bartonella henselae or has_material_basis_in Bartonella quintana. The disease is characterized by the proliferation of blood vessels, resulting in them forming tumour-like masses in the skin and other organs.

name: Native American myopathy
description: A neuromuscular disease characterized by congenital weakness, arthrogryposis, cleft palate, ptosis, myopathic facies, short stature, kykphoscoliosis, talipes deformities and susceptibility to malignant hyperthermia provoked by anesthesia; that has material basis in homozygous mutation in the STAC3 gene on chromosome 12q13.

name: acrorenal syndrome
